      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/rethinking-adult-adhd/202404/adhd-an-18th-century-condition-in-the-21st-century-world"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2024-04/pexels-suzy-hazelwood-1172018.jpg?itok=YfOfo2YI" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="Suzy Hazelwood/Pexels" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/rethinking-adult-adhd/202404/adhd-an-18th-century-condition-in-the-21st-century-world" title="ADHD: An 18th-Century Condition in the 21st-Century World"> ADHD: An 18th-Century Condition in the 21st-Century World </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            So you think that ADHD is the result of the 21st century lifestyle in the United States? Maybe not.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

